<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06075053 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06075053 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Gates  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  LOS-ANGELES; POLICE; OFFICIAL; OPINION  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Police Chief Daryl F. Gates listened grim-faced Thursday to a parade ofcivil-rights leaders and politicians demanding his ouster.;    Clamor forGates' resignation in the wake of the videotaped March 3 police attack onRodney King reached feverish proportions at the weekly Police Commissionhearing, where a boisterous overflow crowd screamed and chanted.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  L.A. CROWD CLAMORS FOR GATES TO BE FIRED  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     &quot;Get rid of the bum!&quot; shouted a member of the audience after NAACP leaderJoseph Duff called for the commission to solve problems of police abuse inminority communities.;    &quot;Your job as law-enforcement officers is not tobring about agitation for war but for peace,&quot; Duff said.;    After the raucoushearing, Gates held a news conference to declare that the statements had notchanged his mind. He didn't speak during the four-hour commission session.;   &quot;I'm not going anywhere. Anyone who thinks I'm going to slink away is wrong,&quot;said Gates, labeling much of what he heard &quot;poppycock and misinformation.&quot;;   A county grand jury investigating the King beating was expected to hand downindictments against at least three police officers involved in the Lake ViewTerrace attack. Twelve other officers may also be disciplined.;    Officerswho stopped King, after what they claimed was a high-speed chase, clubbed himdozens of times with their batons, kicked him and shot him with an electricstun gun.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Los Angeles  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910315  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  21A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  224  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday March 15, 199100075053,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>